  "detailedReviewAnalysis": [
    {
      "reviewId": "places/ChIJm9zzJnW3yhQRHmF9bN2hrZI/reviews/Ci9DQUlRQUNvZENodHljRjlvT21KMmIzQndXa05YT1dRNFVWVjNOekJ2WlhWUk4yYxAB",
      "text": "From the moment I stepped into the hotel, I was deeply moved by the warm hospitality. I especially remember the gentleman at the entrance who expressed his love for Korea and shared a wonderful conversation about Korean food. His friendliness made me feel right at home from the very beginning.\n\nAs an Accor Platinum member, I was incredibly grateful for the Bosphorus View room upgrade, and the scenery was simply spectacular. It was also a wonderful opportunity to experience the special Ramadan buffet curated by the hotel. The Half-Board (Breakfast & Dinner) meals were of excellent quality, and the traditional ritual dance during dinner was a mesmerizing and unforgettable experience.\n\nHowever, I must mention a disappointing incident during a busy weekend breakfast. We were assigned a table, but another guest was mistakenly seated there. The staff were unaware of the double-booking until I brought it to their attention, and even then, we were left standing with our food for quite some time without a proper apology. This was quite unexpected for a 5-star hotel of this caliber, especially considering how much I enjoyed the rest of the services.\n\nDespite this, the individual staff members truly make this hotel special. The Lounge staff were consistently kind and attentive throughout our stay. My sincere thanks to Chef Mehmet Efir for his thoughtful care every morning, and Zeynepnur at the reception, who assisted us so kindly and professionally during our checkout.\n\nSwissôtel The Bosphorus made my final days in Istanbul truly perfect. I highly recommend this hotel to anyone visiting the city and look forward to returning soon.",
